I"9<p>The subchapter 3.5 of <a href="http://www.stat.columbia.edu/~gelman/book/BDA3.pdf"><strong>Bayesian Data Analysis Third Edition</strong></a> gives distributional results of Bayesian inference for the parameters of a multivariate normal distribution with a <strong>known</strong> variance. <em>Additionally, this article discusses the derivation of those results (Equation 3.13 of the book) in <strong>gory details</strong>.</em></p>

